---
/* ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
   TermsModal — Mariposa House Rules

   Renders site-wide via BaseLayout. Hidden by default. Opens when
   any element on the page dispatches the custom event
       window.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent('mariposa:open-terms'))
   The footer's "Terms & Conditions." button is the primary opener.

   Pattern: native <dialog> for free focus trap, ESC-to-close, and
   backdrop semantics. The element is shown with .showModal() so
   the browser handles inertness of the rest of the page. Backdrop
   click and the corner X also close it. Focus returns to the
   opener element on close.

   Copy is verbatim Stephane (2026-05-24). Twelve sections live as
   structured data in this file: the set is finite, the conventions
   overlay wins on typography, and externalising to markdown would
   buy nothing the dialog needs.

   Typography rules honour the Mariposa design system + conventions
   overlay: Hanken eyebrows in uppercase, Spectral display title,
   gold-deep accents, gold disc bullet markers.
   ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ */

interface Section {
  heading: string;
  /* Each entry is either a paragraph (string) or a bullet list (array).
     Inline strong is supported via the {{strong:phrase}} convention,
     resolved in the template below. Keeps the source data plain. */
  blocks: Array<string | string[]>;
}

